  "prompt": "Which IIT has best Hostel Rooms?",
  "response": "There's no definitive \"best\" IIT for hostel rooms because:\n\n*   **Subjectivity:** What constitutes \"best\" is subjective. Some people prioritize room size, others prioritize cleanliness, amenities, or the social environment.\n*   **Varying Infrastructure:** IITs have different infrastructure and have evolved over time. Newer IITs often have better-maintained facilities. Even within the same IIT, different hostels can vary significantly in quality depending on when they were built/renovated.\n*   **Ongoing Renovations:** Many IITs are constantly renovating and upgrading their hostels, so the situation can change.\n\nHowever, based on general reputation and factors like newer construction and recent renovations, here's a *general* idea (note this is not a definitive ranking and can change):\n\n*   **Newer IITs:** Generally, the newer IITs established in the last 10-15 years (like IIT Mandi, IIT Ropar, IIT Patna, IIT Gandhinagar, IIT Bhubaneswar) are likely to have better-maintained and more modern hostels, as they were built with contemporary standards.\n*   **IIT Gandhinagar:** Often mentioned for having good infrastructure, including hostels.\n*   **IIT Hyderabad:** Is also considered to have good hostel facilities.\n*   **Older IITs:** Older IITs (like IIT Bombay, IIT Delhi, IIT Madras, IIT Kanpur, IIT Kharagpur) have a mix. Some hostels might be quite old but could be in the process of renovation. Others might be newer. The experience varies greatly. They do usually have larger student populations so are more likely to have a broader range of facilities.\n\n**Factors to consider about hostels at any IIT:**\n\n*   **Room Size:** Can vary from single occupancy to triple or even quad occupancy, especially in older hostels. Newer hostels tend to have more double or single rooms.\n*   **Amenities:** Look for things like attached bathrooms (becoming more common in newer hostels), internet connectivity, furniture quality, availability of common rooms, sports facilities, and laundry services.\n*   **Cleanliness and Maintenance:** Newer hostels are generally better maintained, but even older ones can be clean if the administration is proactive.\n*   **Social Environment:** This is very important and dependent on the students who live there. The \"hostel culture\" at each IIT varies.\n*   **Location:** Some hostels might be closer to academic buildings or other facilities, which can be convenient.\n*   **Food:** The quality of the mess food is a major factor. This can vary even within the same IIT.\n\n**How to find more specific information:**\n\n*   **IIT Websites:** Look at the official websites of the IITs. They often have information about hostel facilities.\n*   **Student Forums and Social Media:** Search for IIT student forums (e.g., on Quora, Reddit) and social media groups. You can ask current students about their hostel experiences.\n*   **Alumni Networks:** Reach out to alumni of the IITs to get their perspectives.\n*   **Virtual Tours:** Some IITs offer virtual tours of their campuses, including hostel rooms.\n\nIn conclusion, research individual IITs and specific hostels within them to get a better understanding of the available facilities. Don't rely on blanket statements about which IIT has the \"best\" hostel rooms. Good luck!\n",
